        <h1 id="using-parse--github">Firebase and AngularJS</h1>

<hr />

<h2 id="section-1">Section 1: Getting Started</h2>
<ul>
  <li>
    <h3>Why do you need a database?</h3>
    Database's are an essential part of any application that handles data.
    Databases are not merely containers for your objects allowing you to store and retrieve them.
    They give you extra power over your data allowing you to <strong>query</strong> (ask the database questions)
    and perform various operations such as join which allows you to relate data from two different
    tables together. Most importantly they provide you the infrastructure and reliability to scale
    your application as it grows.
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3>Why Firebase?</h3>
    Databases can be cumbersome to set up. Firebase eliminates a lot of this hassle by both hosting
    the information for your application and providing API's that allow you to interact with this
    stored cloud data from your application. Firebase offers API's for Web Development, Android
    and IOS. Meaning if you provide a service that spans all 3 platforms you just need the 1 database
    interacting with the 3 platforms Firebase API's.
    <img src="/~cs110x/static/img/lab5/fireBase1.png" alt="image1" />
  </li>
</ul>
