          <li>You should now see this prompt<br />
<img src="/~cs110x/static/img/lab5/image18.png" alt="image18" /></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Next you will see<br />
<img src="/~cs110x/static/img/lab5/image19.png" alt="image19" />
        <ul>
          <li>Click ‚ÄúAuthorize application‚Äù<br />
<img src="/~cs110x/static/img/lab5/image20.png" alt="image20" /></li>
          <li>Now you will see the data that OAuth was able to retrieve from GitHub for your login</li>
          <li>If you encounter any type of authentication error when trying to login like the one below:<br />
<img src="/~cs110x/static/img/lab5/image21.png" alt="image21" />
            <ul>
              <li>On the Parse website under your application navigate to <strong>Settings=&gt;General</strong> at the bottom of the page <strong>under User Sessions</strong> make sure all the questions are answered ‚ÄúNo‚Äù<br />
